  "name": "multi-select-feature-parity-20260326-0548",
  "idea": "Multi-select feature parity: the bulk properties panel should expose all the same settings as single-clip editing (effects, position/crop, text, transitions, entrance/exit/continuous animations, volume slider, from/to timing, etc.), not just opacity/speed/mute. Also ensure all single-clip operations work with multi-selection where it makes sense: arrow key track movement, context menu operations (copy, split-at-playhead for each), and live visual feedback during multi-drag. The BulkClipPanel in PropertiesPanel.tsx currently only shows 3 fields \u2014 it needs to match the full ClipPanel feature set with mixed-value handling.",
